<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">494.11/69: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-11T18:00:00-05:00">March 11, 1938—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>45. Your 56, March 10, noon. Department assumes that Japanese inquiry
                            relates to claims arising in your consular district. If so Department
                                <pb facs="0294" n="290" xml:id="pg_290"/> has no objection to your
                            furnishing informally the information requested provided it is made
                            clear that other cases of which you have no knowledge may have arisen
                            and also that the amounts indicated are not necessarily final in all
                            cases.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>